<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideed13fb5-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s1594"><num value="1594">§ 1594.</num><heading> Prohibition against alterations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No person shall detach, alter, deface, or destroy any label provided for in this chapter or the rules and regulations made and promulgated thereunder by the Secretary of Agriculture, or alter or substitute seed in a manner that may defeat the purpose of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ideed13fb6-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1939-08-09/ch615">Aug. 9, 1939, ch. 615</ref>, title IV, § 404, <ref href="/us/stat/53/1286">53 Stat. 1286</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
